  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This prospective and observational cohort studies the morphine consumption difference during
      the first 48 hours after a lung lobectomy between patients operated with a robot assisted or
      a video-assisted technique for a lung cancer lobectomy.

      Second outcome was to search eventual cardiac output difference during the surgery in 100
      patients (50 in each group) using a non invasive monitoring device of cardiac output

      All patients operated between january 2016 and March 2017 for a lung cancer lobectomy were
      included.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
